The paper deals with distributed algorithms for the Backup Placement problem in networks, which is a problem in distributed computing. The paper discusses algorithms for various graph topologies, including wireless networks, social networks, claw-free graphs, trees, forests, planar graphs, and graphs of constant arboricity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with neighborhood independence, which is a property of graphs, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses algorithms for graphs with symmetry breaking problems, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses algorithms for sparse graphs, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
